Hi, Dani.  Good question!

On 3/9/07, Dani Zweig &lt;dani@...&gt; wrote:
&gt;
&gt; I&#39;m trying to adapt the custom filter runner posted by David Saff, but when I
&gt; try to run a test the runner seems to be caught in an infinite instantiation
&gt; loop.  (The behavior is the same whether I am running from ant 1.7 or
&gt; Eclipse 3.2)  Here&#39;s a stripped-down example of the code that is causing
&gt; this to happen.  What am I doing wrong?
&gt; [...]
&gt; public VerboseRunner(Class&lt;?&gt; testClass) throws Exception {
&gt; Request classRequest = Request.aClass(testClass);
&gt; delegate = classRequest.getRunner();
&gt; System.out.println(&quot;Created VerboseRunner with testClass &quot; +
&gt;         testClass);
&gt; }

Here, Request.aClass(testClass).getRunner() will look at the @RunWith
annotation, and will attempt to assign to delegate, you guessed it,
another VerboseRunner, which will call
Request.aClass(testClass).getRunner(), which will...

Probably what you want here is

delegate= new TestClassRunner(testClass);

Let me know if that nails it,

   David Saff
